                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>495 Lexington Av.<lb/>
                New York&#44; 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Jan. 1886.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. and dear Sir&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>I wrote you last on 22nd.<lb/> ult&#44; and trust that the letter duly reached<lb/> you. Since then I have come in possession <lb/> of your postal card of 31st. ult by which<lb/> I was glad to learn that both Drs. Kohut<lb/> amd Drachman had answered you encour&#45;<lb/> agingly. The latter wrote Dr. Mendes ask&#45;<lb/>ing for &#40;about&#41; a hundred of our circulars&#44;<lb/> as he intended addressing his congrega&#45;<lb/>tion on last Friday evening on that and<lb/> kindred subjects&#44; and wanted them for dis&#45;<lb/>tribution. But I regret that I could not<lb/> spare more than about twenty of each&#44; as<lb/> I wanted to have some left for any other<lb/> call that may be made for them&#44; Could I<lb/> have anticipated this&#44; I would have had<lb/> more printed.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>The President promised Dr. Mendes and myself<lb/> a meeting of the Board of Trustees&#44; on last Tues&#45;<lb/>day&#44; but thro&#39; a mistake it was called for the pre&#45;<lb/>vious evening&#44; and therefore we were not present. The<lb/> next will be on Thursday evening 7th Inst. and after<lb/> that I hope to be able to write you definitely when<lb/> to visit this city for an interchange of views with<lb/> those favoring the cause. The &#34;Am. Heb.&#34; &#34;Heb. Standard&#34;&#44;<lb/> and &#34;H. Journal&#44;&#34; &#40;the three Jewish papers which I have<lb/> seen&#41; give it their support. Activity and perseverance<lb/> on our part will&#44; I believe&#44; with God&#39;s help&#44; carry<lb/> it through. Do you not think it would help us if you<lb/> write to Dr. Schneeberger&#63;&#45;&#45;As I anticipated&#44; my<lb/> sister&#44; Mrs. Saml. Piza&#44; is willing to raise their sub. to<lb/> &#36;1000&#44;&#44; &#40;one thousand&#41;. With a few more such and small&#45;<lb/>er am&#91;oun&#93;ts&#44; we could make a start and rely on general<lb/> annual contributions of from &#36;5 to &#36;20. from members<lb/> and patrons throughout the U.S. for its support in the<lb/> future. You are doubtless giving the matter your con&#45;<lb/>sideration to enable you to give the outline of some plan<lb/> when you visit us. Yours truly&#44; David M. Piza<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais&#44; Phila.<lb/></p>
            </body>
